$Id$
------------------------------------------------------------

xindy (`fleXible INDexing sYstem') is a flexible index-processor. See
the files in directory ./Doc for a detailed description of what xindy
does.


This distribution is also available at

	ftp://ftp.th-darmstadt.de/pub/tex/src/xindy/

or at our homepage at

	http://www.iti.informatik.th-darmstadt.de/xindy/

which contains the most up-to-date information about xindy.

Currently we support binary-distributions for the following platforms:

    Linux ELF			i386
    AIX-3.2			rs6000
    HP-UX 9.x			hppa
    Solaris 2.4, 2.5, 2.5.1     sun4m/sun4u
    IRIX 5.3			mips (available soon)

Everybody is encouraged to port xindy to new platforms. For any kind
of suggestions, helpful comments, questions, bug reports and such,
please mail to the xindy mailing-list

	xindy@iti.informatik.th-darmstadt.de

You can subscribe to the list by sending a mail to

	xindy-request@iti.informatik.th-darmstadt.de

containing `subscribe xindy' in the mail body.


See file INSTALL for a description how to install this distribution.


